# AI service (Python / FastAPI)

## Patterns

- Entry: `main.py`. Deterministic risk/simulation math must stay predictable and match .NET `ScenarioMath` behaviour.
- LLM provider chain via `LLM_PROVIDERS` / `LLM_PROVIDER=auto`. Missing API keys skip that provider; final fallback is canned text (tag `· offline fallback`).
- Endpoints: `/predict`, `/simulate`, `/project-brief`, `/weekly-recap`, `/chat-step` (stateless; .NET orchestrator runs tools).

## Rules

- Never let the LLM override computed `risk_level`, `delay_days`, or scenario impact numbers — narrative fields only.
- Keep timeouts env-driven (`LLM_TIMEOUT_SECS`, `OLLAMA_TIMEOUT_SECS`).
- Add pytest coverage in `ai-service/tests/` for new provider logic or math changes.

## Local run

```powershell
cd ai-service
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
```
